Starting from germline variants (SNVs and indels)16, a series of filters were applied. First, heterozygous calls with Variant Allele Frequency (VAF) deviating from 50% by more than 2.6 standard deviations and homozygous calls with VAF less than 95% were removed. Second, variants were removed if their Minor Allele Frequency (MAF) in EACs was > 10% and substantially larger than in ExAC64 and in the European cohort from 1000 Genomes27 using the following formula:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
